### Export JSON representation of a Lexical Node

Source: https://github.com/facebook/lexical/blob/main/packages/lexical-website/docs/concepts/serialization.md

Implement `exportJSON()` to define how a custom LexicalNode is serialized into a JSON object. This method should extend the superclass's serialization by invoking `super.exportJSON()` and adding any custom properties. Lexical traverses the editor state, calling this method on each node during JSON export.

```javascript
export type SerializedLexicalNode = {
  type: string;
  version: number;
};

exportJSON(): SerializedLexicalNode
```

```javascript
export type SerializedHeadingNode = Spread< {
    tag: 'h1' | 'h2' | 'h3' | 'h4' | 'h5' | 'h6';
  },
  SerializedElementNode
>;

exportJSON(): SerializedHeadingNode {
  return {
    ...super.exportJSON(),
    tag: this.getTag(),
  };
}
```

