### Import JSON representation into a Lexical Node

Source: https://github.com/facebook/lexical/blob/main/packages/lexical-website/docs/concepts/serialization.md

Implement `importJSON()` to deserialize a JSON object back into a LexicalNode. This method uses the `type` field from the JSON to map to the correct Lexical node class. It's recommended to use `updateFromJSON` within `importJSON` for simplified implementation and extensibility.

```typescript
export type SerializedLexicalNode = {
  type: string;
  version: number;
};

importJSON(jsonNode: SerializedLexicalNode): LexicalNode
```

```typescript
static importJSON(serializedNode: SerializedHeadingNode): HeadingNode {
  return $createHeadingNode().updateFromJSON(serializedNode);
}

updateFromJSON(
  serializedNode: LexicalUpdateJSON<SerializedHeadingNode>,
): this {
  return super.updateFromJSON(serializedNode).setTag(serializedNode.tag);
}
```

