### LexicalNode.updateFromJSON()

Source: https://github.com/facebook/lexical/blob/main/packages/lexical-website/docs/concepts/serialization.md

`updateFromJSON` simplifies the implementation of `importJSON` by allowing base classes to expose code for setting node properties from JSON to subclasses.

```APIDOC
## LexicalNode.updateFromJSON()

### Description
`updateFromJSON` is a method introduced in Lexical 0.23 to simplify the implementation of `importJSON`. It allows a base class to expose the code used to set all node properties based on JSON to any subclass.

### Method
```
updateFromJSON(serializedNode: LexicalUpdateJSON<SerializedHeadingNode>): this
```

### Request Example
```json
{
  "type": "myNode",
  "version": 1,
  "newProperty": "optional value"
}
```

### Response
#### Success Response (200)
- **this** - The updated node instance.

### Response Example
```typescript
updateFromJSON(serializedNode: LexicalUpdateJSON<SerializedHeadingNode>): this {
  return super.updateFromJSON(serializedNode).setTag(serializedNode.tag);
}
```
```

