### Serialize and Parse Editor State

Source: https://github.com/facebook/lexical/blob/main/packages/lexical-website/docs/intro.md

Shows how to serialize the current Lexical editor state to a JSON string and how to parse a JSON string back into an editor state. This is useful for saving and restoring editor content.

```javascript
import { createEditor } from 'lexical';

const editor = createEditor();

// Assume editor has some state...

// Serialize the editor state to JSON
const editorStateJSON = JSON.stringify(editor.getEditorState().toJSON());
console.log('Serialized state:', editorStateJSON);

// To restore from JSON:
const newEditorState = editor.parseEditorState(JSON.parse(editorStateJSON));
editor.setEditorState(newEditorState);
console.log('Restored editor state.');

```

