### Define SerializedTextNode for Versioning

Source: https://github.com/facebook/lexical/blob/main/packages/lexical-website/docs/concepts/serialization.md

Demonstrates how to define the serialized type for Lexical's TextNode, including its properties like `detail`, `format`, `mode`, `style`, and `text`. It also shows how to add new optional fields for future changes without causing breaking changes.

```typescript
import type {Spread} from 'lexical';

export type SerializedTextNode = Spread< {
    detail: number;
    format: number;
    mode: TextModeType;
    style: string;
    text: string;
  },
  SerializedLexicalNode
>;

// Example with a new optional field
export type SerializedTextNode = Spread< {
    detail: number;
    format: number;
    mode: TextModeType;
    style: string;
    text: string;
    // Our new field we've added
    newField?: string,
  },
  SerializedLexicalNode
>;
```

