### Parse and Serialize Lexical Editor State

Source: https://github.com/facebook/lexical/blob/main/README.md

Illustrates how to serialize an Editor State to JSON and parse it back into the editor. This is essential for saving and loading editor content, enabling features like persistence and state restoration.

```javascript
const currentEditorState = editor.getEditorState();

// Serialize the current editor state to JSON
const serializedEditorState = JSON.stringify(currentEditorState.toJSON());

console.log('Serialized State:', serializedEditorState);

// To parse it back into the editor:
const newEditorState = editor.parseEditorState(serializedEditorState);
editor.setEditorState(newEditorState);
```

